  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT311-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">alar añciya talaimakaḷ talaimakaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉākat tōḻikkuc coṟṟatu </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Uttered by HER, who is afraid of gossip, as if talking
          to the confidante, while HE is behind the hedge. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT311">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> alaryāṅ koḻiva tōḻi peruṅkaṭaṟ</l>
          <l> pulavunā ṟakaṉṟuṟai valavaṉ ṟāṅkavu</l>
          <l> nillātu kaḻinta kalleṉ kaṭuntēr</l>
          <l> yāṉkaṇ ṭaṉṟō vilaṉē pāṉā</l>
          <l> ḷōṅkal veṇmaṇaṟ ṟāḻnta puṉṉait</l>
          <l> tātucēr nikarmalar koyyu</l>
          <l> māya mellā muṭaṉkaṇ ṭaṉṟē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>How will gossip cease, <note place="foot"> Is there a special nuance to the pl. of alar (visible in the n.pl. <term xml:lang="ta"> oḻiva </term>)? One might consider rendering it "rumours".   </note> friend?</l>
          <l rend="indent8">By the great sea,</l>
          <l>As for seeing the rattling, quick chariot</l>
          <l rend="indent2">which passed by without stopping,</l>
          <l rend="indent4">although <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> tāṅka-vum </term>: the infinitive plus <term xml:lang="ta"> -um </term> presumably has to be taken in a concessive sense. But what is the impact of this line? That HE actually wanted to stop, but did not dare because he did not find HER alone?   </note> the charioteer restrained [it]</l>
          <l rend="indent7">in the wide ghat smelling of fish</l>
          <l rend="indent9">– not me.</l>
          <l>On midday it was visible <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> kaṇṭaṉṟu </term>, n.sg., has to be construed as an intransitive here, i.e. in the sense of "becoming visible".     </note> for all the girl companions,</l>
          <l rend="indent">plucking lustrous blossoms joined with pollen</l>
          <l rend="indent2">of the Puṉṉai tree which hung down into the rising white sands.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
